13. "He alone is free who lives with free consent under the entire guidance of reason."
14. "He who lives according to the guidance of reason endeavors, as far as he can, to repay hatred with love."
15. "A free man thinks of death least of all things; and his wisdom is a meditation not of death but of life."
16. "We feel and know that we are eternal."
17. "The more clearly you understand yourself and your emotions, the more you become a lover of what is."
18. "Nature abhors a vacuum."
19. "If you want the present to be different from the past, study the past."
20. "Nothing in nature is random. A thing appears random only through the incompleteness of our knowledge."
